.Dd Nov 12, 2025
.Dt gufi_getfattr
.Os Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm gufi_getfattr
.Nd GUFI version of
.Xr getfattr 1
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op options
.Op path...

.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a wrapper around
.Xr gufi_query 1 , which performs queries on the contents of a GUFI tree in a parallel manner.

The input arguments and output are intended to be reminicent of
.Xr getfattr 1 with --no-defereence --physical always set.

.Sh OPTIONS

.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It Fl -help
show this help message and exit
.It Fl v, -version
show program's version number and exit
.It Fl n NAME, -name NAME
Dump the values of the named extended attribute
.It Fl d, -dump
Dump the values of all extended attributes associated with pathname
.It Fl m PATTERN, -match PATTERN
Only include attributes with names matching the regular expression pattern. The default
value for pattern is "^user\.", which includes all the attributes in the user namespace.
Specify "-" for including all attributes. Refer to attr(5) for a more detailed discussion
of namespaces.
.It Fl -only-values
Dump out the raw extended attribute value(s) without encoding them
.It Fl R -recursive
List the atttributes of all files and directories recursively
.It Fl -delim\ c
Delimiter separating output columns
.It Fl -in-memory-name\ name
Name of in-memory database when aggregation is performed
.It Fl -aggregate-name\ name
Name of final database when aggregation is performed
.It Fl -skip-file\ filename
Name of file containing directory basenames to skip
.It Fl V, -verbose
Show the gufi_query being executed
.El

.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It EXIT_SUCCESS or EXIT_FAILURE
.El

.Pp
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width -compact
.It gufi_getfattr
.It @INSTALL_CONFIG@
.El

\# .Sh BUGS
\# .Sh EXAMPLE

.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr gufi_du 1 ,
.Xr gufi_find 1 ,
.Xr gufi_ls 1 ,
.Xr gufi_stats 1 ,
.Xr gufi_query 1
